<br>
She was now feeling like if she had no identity, she never felt she belonged to the Roman Empire, and she was feeling that the Amazons would ever consider her as a Roman stranger. And she was hating Rome's imperialism and patriarchy, having been the victim of a violent father, her best friend Myrene, an  Amazon working as priestess in the Artemision having been murdered by three drunken Roman soldiers, her life threatened. And she was terribly worried for Octavia, her ill mother and Margarita Cecilia, her 15 years old sister who had stayed in Ephesus to take care of her mother. But she had to flee, or would have been killed. Or by the violent fiancé her father had given her, or by her father himself. In Roman law, the father had the right to kill his wife and children if they were resisting to his authority. And Livia not only refused to marry her fiancé, but also accused him of having participated in Myrene's assassination, having been the only witness of the cold blooded murder of the young priestess.<br>
<br>
Livia was hating Rome as no one<br>
<br>
&quot; I'm one of yours, Livia Diana, from Chadesia. But I was born in Ephesus, Roman by birth, Amazon by choice&quot; she responded politely,in all honesty but at the same time looking like asking her if she was considerating her as one of her sisters or as a stranger. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/usheyala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheyala</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 440<br> <font color=#993300>(6/26/02 11:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Friend or Foe?</span><hr size=1> Shey swallowed and smiled.<br>
