<br>
&quot;If your a Roman then why do you worship the Greek gods?&quot;<br>
<br>
Ardyn stopped trusting Romans easily when one of them killed Tyger, her mother. She didn't even trust Sarabi Falco, the High Priestess of Athena. Sarabi was a very good friend of The Vasilissa, Varia.<br>
<br>
Ardyn still had mailce in her heart from the death that had surrounded her. Outsiders like Zelia, Hope, and Carlira had tried to bring down the Amazons and each time Ardyn's heart would grow colder to newcomers.<br>
<br>
She trusted Sheyala because of her connections with Hippolyte. Hippolyte is a living legend to all Amazons, God worshipping or not.<br>
<br>
Ardyn chewed her bread waiting for an answer. <p>~Ardyn O The Wind~<BR> =¤= Amazon Goddess of Virtue =¤=<BR>=ll= Re-Incarnation of the Warrior Shaman Otere=ll=<BR>*Amazon Warrior Shamaness*<BR> "What we do in Life echoes in eternity."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=livia>Livia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#993300>(6/27/02 10:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mrmagoo.fortunecity.com/bowser/marion.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An Untrusting to Romans</span><hr size=1> &quot; I heard in Ephesus that there was a Goddess, guardian of wildlife, caretaker of women and children, free, independent...Since that day I felt drawn to Artemis and visited the Artemision, it was for me a place of peace, prayer and harmony and I wanted to become a priestess, but never got the chance. My best friend was a priestess of Artemis and she changed my life forever...&quot;<br>
<br>
Her voice broke as she remembered the tragic fate of Myrene, a young Amazon orphaned when Roman soldiers invaded her village and killed Myrene's mother and sister. The child had been found by priestesses of Artemis wandering alone around the Artemision and adopted and raised by them in the temple. Her short life had ended when three drunken Roman soldiers attacked her in the forest, one of them was the fiancé given to Livia. It was Livia herself who had found the unfortunate Myrene and brought her to the temple and she had fought for her friend's life as well as the priestesses who had adopted her. But hopelessly, Myrene gave her last breath in front of her despaired Roman friend who fought to make justice made, denouncing those crimes, she became herself a target, had been severely beaten by her father and had to flee to save her life. To be identified to those criminals was breaking her heart<br>
<br>
&quot; My people committed horrible crimes, invaded nations, but we aren't all bad, I've never been proud of my Roman identity but I have to accept it.I'm a woman of the people, not a soldier and had my share of suffering, I suffered from my own people's patriarchic system, corruption and imperialism, more than you could ever think. But I have no power on my people as I'm a woman, and in Rome and her colonies, women have no rights. If I was born in nobility, maybe I could have more influence but I'm not. But what is Rome, an idea, an illusion... I'm a human like you and if Rome would invade Chadesia, I promise that I would fight at your side. Please don't think that all Romans are enemies of the Amazons, I share your grief and more than you could ever think. What could I do to be trusted by you and no more being judged for my Roman blood rather than who I am&quot;<br>
<br>
Once again, Livia was feeling that terrible duality and like an apatrid, born as Roman but Amazon by soul. Accepted by none. Hated by many Romans, distrusted by many Amazons... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uamznlyli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AmznLyli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#993300>(6/28/02 11:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: An Untrusting to Romans</span><hr size=1> ::Lyliane listened to them silently as she walked over to the falls quietly. She watched them as she sat down and took off her boots, slipping her feet into the cool water. The young girl sympathized with the one called Livia. Lyliane was neither Amazon by blood, nor was she Roman, but she knew what it was to not be accepted for who you were. She stood and walked over to them, smiling to Livia and nodding to Shey and Ardyn. Robin had pointed them out to her, but she hadn't met them formally yet.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uardynothewind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ardyn O The Wind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#993300>(6/28/02 1:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=58.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://hometown.aol.com/thegooddochl6/images/jmoore.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Imbalance</span><hr size=1> On any other day, Ardyn would have trusted this newcomer....but something was off balance in the Northern Amazon unity...Ardyn had yet to learn of Yakut's break of the path of peace. When, a Northern Amazon is off balance so is every other Northern Amazon.<br>
<br>
Ardyn's soul was the Re-Incarnation of Otere, Yakut's best friend and adopted sister. She was one of the most affected by this Imbalance.<br>
<br>
